article.headline: Hartford 64, Albany, N.Y. 62
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Joe Zeglinski scored 21 points and Hartford held off Albany (N.Y.) down the stretch to come away with a 64-62 victory on Wednesday night. Joel Barkers hit a free throw to give the Stags (6-15, 4-4 America East Conference) a 64-62 lead with 35 seconds left. Albany's Jake Lindfors missed a jumper with 5 seconds left and Logan Aronhalt missed a 3 with 2 seconds to play. Albany (6-17, 1-7) has lost three straight and seven of its past eight games. Hartford trailed 43-42, but scored six straight points to take a 48-43 lead on Joel Barkers' jumper with 11:31 to play. Albany tied the game at 55 on Scotty McRae's layup with 5:32 left. McRae scored all nine of his points in the second half. Morgan Sabia added 12 points for Hartford, which was 9-for-24 from the 3-point line (37.5 percent). Aronhalt scored 14 and Tim Ambrose had 10 points and six assists for Albany.
